These are tools maintained by Jean-Charles Lambert. We try to
maintain the latest/stable versions here, but if you need to
patch/experiment with something more recent, here are the 
recipes:


unsio:   (see also: https://simutools.docs.lam.fr/unsio/)
`   git clone https://gitlab.lam.fr/simutools/unsio/
    mknemo unsio

    this also needs: libsqlite3-dev (ubuntu) or libsq3-devel (fedora)
    as well as HDF5: libhdf5-serial-dev hdf5-tools (ubuntu)
    
python wrapper for unsio: (see also : https://pypi.org/project/unsio/)
    To read/write in NEMO format or Gadget1,2,3 or RAMSES 
    install unsio python wrapper with a simple command
    
    pip install unsio --user
    
    and visit :
    https://simutools.docs.lam.fr/unsio/Guide/python_guide_reading/

glnemo2: (see also: http://projets.lam.fr/projects/glnemo2)
    git clone https://gitlab.lam.fr/jclamber/glnemo2.git
    mknemo glnemo2

uns_projects (see also: https://projets.lam.fr/projects/uns_projects)
    git clone https://gitlab.lam.fr/jclamber/uns_projects
    mknemo uns_projects

python wrapper for falcON and unsio tools (see https://pypi.org/project/python-unsiotools/)
    pip install python-unsiotools -U
    
